title: As Last Module Docks, China Completes Its Space Station
description: The Mengtian module was launched into orbit and docked with the Tiangong space station, the latest step in Beijing’s effort to surpass the United States in space exploration.
dc:creator: Keith Bradsher
media:description: The Mengtian module, with the Long March rocket that would take it into orbit, at China’s launch site in Hainan Province last week.
